"use strict";(self.webpackChunknfdi_sections=self.webpackChunknfdi_sections||[]).push([[5676],{6790:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report","metadata":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report","editUrl":"https://github.com/nfdi-de/nfdi-sections/edit/main/blog/blog/2026-04-16-2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-16-2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report.md","title":"Report on the 2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop Now Published on Zenodo","description":"The report on the 2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop has been published on Zenodo. It documents the outcomes of a three-day workshop held on June 25\u201327, 2025, in Hannover, organized by the Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance.","date":"2026-04-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Section Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/metadata","description":"Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance"},{"inline":false,"label":"Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/metadata-tag","description":"Topics related to metadata standards and schemas"},{"inline":false,"label":"Taskforce Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/taskforce-metadata","description":"Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance"},{"inline":false,"label":"NFDI Metadata Profile","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/nfdi-metadata-profile","description":"NFDI Core Metadata Profile development"}],"readingTime":2.54,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Oliver Koepler","title":"Spokesperson Section Metadata","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","page":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/authors/okoepler"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","github":"https://github.com/okoepler"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39139700?v=4","key":"okoepler"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report","title":"Report on the 2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop Now Published on Zenodo","authors":["okoepler"],"tags":["Meta","metadata","taskforce-metadata","nfdi-metadata-profile"],"date":"2026-04-16T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Recommendation on Registering NFDI Repositories in re3data Now Published","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/re3data-recommendation-nfdi-repositories"}},"content":"The report on the [2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19709639) has been published on Zenodo. It documents the outcomes of a three-day workshop held on June 25\u201327, 2025, in Hannover, organized by the Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Why a Workshop Series on Metadata?\\n\\nMetadata standardisation is one of the core cross-cutting challenges of the NFDI. The *Bund-L\xe4nder-Vereinbarung (BLV)*, the foundational agreement between the German federal and state governments establishing the NFDI, explicitly mandates that consortia adhere to established metadata standards. The NFDI Strategy 2025/2026 reinforces this by calling for the harmonisation of diverse metadata formats across scientific disciplines to enhance the efficiency and interoperability of the entire research data ecosystem.\\n\\nTo address this mandate, the Taskforce Metadata \u2014 embedded in the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance \u2014 was established with the goal of promoting the adoption of cross-disciplinary terminologies and metadata schemas across all NFDI consortia. The Taskforce identified three generic metadata standards as primary candidates: the **Data Catalog Vocabulary Application Profile (DCAT-AP)**, the **DataCite Metadata Schema**, and **Schema.org**. Rather than imposing a single schema, the strategy follows a three-stage approach: identify and evaluate existing schemas, encourage harmonised adoption, and facilitate the integration of modular, domain-specific extensions.\\n\\nThe workshop series is the central instrument for advancing this agenda through broad community participation.\\n\\n## From Schema Selection to Practical Implementation\\n\\nThe **1st NFDI Metadata Workshop** (January 14\u201315, 2025, Dresden) brought together approximately 50 metadata experts representing all 26 NFDI consortia. It established that a single, uniform metadata schema is not feasible across the full breadth of NFDI disciplines, but that a shared set of core fields \u2014 covering aspects like identifier, title, creator, and license \u2014 could form the basis for cross-consortia interoperability. The report is available on Zenodo: [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15227235.](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15227235).\\n\\nThe **2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop** shifted the focus from schema selection to the challenges of practical implementation. The central outcome is a first formulation of a **NFDI Core Metadata Profile**: a schema-agnostic baseline defining a minimal set of required metadata fields that must be populated regardless of the underlying technical format. A number of elements were discussed and afterwards catgorized as **mandatory**, **recommended**, and **optional**\\nThe workshop also addressed the inherent limitations of schema mapping (all cross-schema mappings are lossy and use-case specific), presented domain-specific metadata extensions from five NFDI communities, and advanced a **layered metadata model** combining a shared core with discipline-specific extensions.\\n\\nA third metadata workshop is already in planning to continue developing the NFDI Core Metadata Profile and to advance discussions on discipline-specific metadata layers.\\n\\n## Reference\\nHenzen, C., Neidiger, C., S\xf6ding, E., & Trippel, T. (2025). Report on the first NFDI Metadata Workshop. Zenodo. [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15227235](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15227235)\\n\\nFliegl, H., Henzen, C., Koepler, O., Stervbo, U., S\xf6ding, E., & Trippel, T. (2025). *Report on the 2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop*. Zenodo. [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19709639](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19709639)"},{"id":"re3data-recommendation-nfdi-repositories","metadata":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/re3data-recommendation-nfdi-repositories","editUrl":"https://github.com/nfdi-de/nfdi-sections/edit/main/blog/blog/2026-04-14-re3data-recommendation.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-14-re3data-recommendation.md","title":"Recommendation on Registering NFDI Repositories in re3data Now Published","description":"The Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance has published the draft of a recommendation for registering and curating NFDI research data repositories in re3data \u2014 the registry of research data repositories.","date":"2026-04-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Section Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/metadata","description":"Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance"},{"inline":false,"label":"Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/metadata-tag","description":"Topics related to metadata standards and schemas"},{"inline":false,"label":"re3data","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/re3data","description":"Registry of Research Data Repositories"},{"inline":false,"label":"Repositories","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/repositories","description":"Research data repositories"},{"inline":false,"label":"Taskforce Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/taskforce-metadata","description":"Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance"}],"readingTime":1.78,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Oliver Koepler","title":"Spokesperson Section Metadata","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","page":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/authors/okoepler"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","github":"https://github.com/okoepler"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39139700?v=4","key":"okoepler"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"re3data-recommendation-nfdi-repositories","title":"Recommendation on Registering NFDI Repositories in re3data Now Published","authors":["okoepler"],"tags":["Meta","metadata","re3data","repositories","taskforce-metadata"],"date":"2026-04-14T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Report on the 2nd NFDI Metadata Workshop Now Published on Zenodo","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/2nd-nfdi-metadata-workshop-report"},"nextItem":{"title":"Invitation: Section Meta Meeting \u2013 31 March 2026","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/section-meta-meeting-march-2026"}},"content":"The Taskforce Metadata of the NFDI Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance has published the draft of a recommendation for registering and curating NFDI research data repositories in [re3data](https://www.re3data.org) \u2014 the registry of research data repositories.\\n\\nThe recommendation document is now open for comments by the NFDI community and should be published as a NFDI standard in the future.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nThe recommendation addresses NFDI consortia and members who operate or are responsible for research data repositories. Its two central objectives are to increase the **findability and visibility** of NFDI-relevant repositories, and to ensure **sustainable, quality-assured descriptions** of those repositories within re3data, including up-to-date information on implemented metadata standards.\\n\\nBeyond registration, NFDI repositories are to be labelled within re3data, supporting the long-term goal of establishing an NFDI-endorsed quality mark for trusted repositories. re3data is defined as the **minimum standard** for repository registration across NFDI; consortia remain free to additionally register in domain-specific or other relevant registries such as FAIRsharing.\\n\\nThe document was developed through a community consensus process within the Taskforce and the Section, drawing on discussions from both NFDI Metadata Workshops (Dresden 2025, Hannover 2025). It was endorsed by the Section on 31 March 2026 and published on Zenodo on 14 April 2026, opening a community comment phase open until 18 May 2026.\\n\\n## On the Path to an Official NFDI Standard\\nThe recommendation is explicitly designed to become a NFDI Standard. The process builds upon the current draft of Leitfaden zur Entwicklung von NFDI Standards and includes a structured governance roadmap: after the community comment phase closes in May, a revised draft will go to a vote by official Section members, followed by a presentation and vote at the Konsortialversammlung in. Final approval as an official NFDI Standard is targeted for autumn 2026 by the scientific senate.\\n\\n\\n\\n**Reference:** Castro, L. J., Fliegl, H., Henzen, C., L\xf6be, M., Koepler, O., Neidiger, C., S\xf6ding, E., Trippel, T., Stervbo, U., & Wiljes, C. (2026). *Empfehlung an die Konsortien und Mitglieder des Vereins Nationale Forschungsdateninfrastruktur (NFDI) e.V. zum Nachweis von NFDI-Datenrepositorien in re3data.* Zenodo. [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19565419](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19565419)"},{"id":"section-meta-meeting-march-2026","metadata":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/section-meta-meeting-march-2026","editUrl":"https://github.com/nfdi-de/nfdi-sections/edit/main/blog/blog/2026-03-06-section-meta-meeting-invitation.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-06-section-meta-meeting-invitation.md","title":"Invitation: Section Meta Meeting \u2013 31 March 2026","description":"We warmly invite all NFDI members and other interested parties to join the upcoming Section Meta meeting on 31 March 2026 at 4:00 pm (CET).","date":"2026-03-06T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Section Metadata","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/tags/metadata","description":"Section Metadata, Terminologies, Provenance"}],"readingTime":0.57,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Oliver Koepler","title":"Spokesperson Section Metadata","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","page":{"permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/authors/okoepler"},"socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-koepler-b55a995/","github":"https://github.com/okoepler"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39139700?v=4","key":"okoepler"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"section-meta-meeting-march-2026","title":"Invitation: Section Meta Meeting \u2013 31 March 2026","authors":["okoepler"],"tags":["Meta"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Recommendation on Registering NFDI Repositories in re3data Now Published","permalink":"/nfdi-sections/blog/re3data-recommendation-nfdi-repositories"}},"content":"We warmly invite all NFDI members and other interested parties to join the upcoming **Section Meta meeting** on **31 March 2026 at 4:00 pm (CET)**.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nThe meeting will cover the following topics:\\n\\n- **Presentation and discussion** \u2013 Proposal for the Ramp-Up phase of the TS4NFDI Basic Service project\\n- **Presentation and discussion** \u2013 \\"Recommendation to members of NFDI e.V. for the registration of NFDI data repositories in re3data\\"\\n- **Presentation** \u2013 NFDI Sections Knowledge Base\\n- **Updates from the Working Groups**\\n\\nThe meeting is open to everyone with an interest in research data metadata and NFDI infrastructure. We look forward to seeing you there!\\n\\nFor connection details, please watch for the meeting announcement on the Section Meta mailing list."}]}}')}}]);